(Sales & Footfall Performance – H1, H2, H3, H4)
1. 📌 Objective

The objective of this report is to evaluate and justify performance against Key Result Areas (KRAs) focused on Sales and Footfall, using CRM data across multiple half-yearly periods (H1, H2, H3, H4).

2. 📅 Data Coverage

The analysis is based on half-yearly performance:

H1: April – September
H2: October – March
H3 & H4: Subsequent yearly half cycles

The data spans multiple financial years, enabling trend-based performance evaluation.

3. 📊 Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)

The following KPIs have been considered:

Total Customers (Footfall Indicator)
Total Bills (Sales Activity Indicator)
New Customers (Customer Acquisition)
Repeat Customers (Customer Retention & Loyalty)
New to Repeat Conversion (Customer Engagement Effectiveness)
Number of Stores (Business Expansion Impact)
4. 📈 Footfall Performance Analysis
Footfall has been evaluated using Total Customers data across all half-year periods.
A comparative analysis of H1 vs H2 shows seasonal variations and growth trends.
Growth in customer count reflects improved store visibility, marketing effectiveness, and customer attraction strategies.

✅ Justification:
Consistent or increasing footfall indicates strong market presence and successful customer acquisition strategies.

5. 💰 Sales Performance Analysis
Sales performance is analyzed through Total Bills, representing transaction volume.
Higher bill counts indicate improved conversion rates and revenue generation capability.
Comparison across H1, H2, H3, H4 highlights business growth and seasonal sales impact.

✅ Justification:
Increase in bills directly supports achievement of sales targets and reflects strong execution at store level.

6. 🔄 Customer Conversion & Retention
New Customers: Reflect marketing success and new customer onboarding.
Repeat Customers: Indicate customer satisfaction and loyalty.
New to Repeat Conversion: Shows effectiveness in converting first-time buyers into loyal customers.

✅ Justification:
A strong repeat customer base ensures sustainable revenue growth and reduces dependency on new acquisitions.

7. 🏬 Store Expansion Impact
Increase in number of stores contributes to higher reach and customer base.
Expansion directly impacts both footfall and sales growth.

✅ Justification:
Growth in store network strengthens overall business performance and supports higher KRA achievement.

8. 📊 H1 vs H2 vs H3 vs H4 Insights
H2 periods generally show higher performance due to festive and wedding seasons.
Strong performance in H1 indicates operational strength during off-season.
Year-on-year improvement across all halves reflects consistent business growth.
